      "code": "def predict_next_frame(frame, action, xy=None):\n    \"\"\"\n    Predict the next frame for the grid game.\n\n    This implementation follows a deterministic rule:\n    - If the action is ACTION6 and a coordinate (x, y) is provided,\n      it will change cells in the bottom row (row index 63) that currently\n      have the value 3 to 4. The columns to modify are determined by a simple\n      hash of the coordinates: (x * 31 + y * 17) modulo 64.\n    - For all other actions, the frame is returned unchanged.\n\n    Parameters\n    ----------\n    frame : list[list[int]]\n        A 64x64 grid of integers in the range 0\u201115.\n    action : str\n        One of 'ACTION1' \u2026 'ACTION7'.\n    xy : tuple[int, int] or None\n        The (x, y) coordinate for ACTION6; ignored otherwise.\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    list[list[int]]\n        The predicted next frame.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Deep copy the frame to avoid mutating the input\n    new_frame = [row[:] for row in frame]\n\n    if action == \"ACTION6\" and xy is not None:\n        x, y = xy\n        # Compute a deterministic column index from the coordinates\n        col = (x * 31 + y * 17) % 64\n\n        # Change the cell at (row=63, col) if it currently holds a 3\n        if new_frame[63][col] == 3:\n            new_frame[63][col] = 4\n\n        # Additionally, also modify the next column to emulate observed pairs\n        next_col = (col + 1) % 64\n        if new_frame[63][next_col] == 3:\n            new_frame[63][next_col] = 4\n\n    return new_frame"
